---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Now">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8 pt-16 pb-24">

    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Now</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-light text-stone-900 mb-2">What I'm doing</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-400">Updated April 2026 · Ballwin, Missouri</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-base text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Building</h2>
        <p>
          Finishing the last features on Smarter Travel Planner — trip sharing, subscription payments,
          the AI concierge that makes the whole thing work. It's close. The goal is a clean demo-ready
          version before summer.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Also building the travel journal engine: a local app that processes 140,000 photos alongside
          Google Timeline data to generate readable, honest travel writing. Ljubljana is already done.
          A lot more to publish.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Advising</h2>
        <p>
          Working with health tech startups through BioSTL. The companies are early-stage,
          the problems are real, and the work is genuinely interesting.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Planning</h2>
        <p>
          The next trip. Always the next trip. Porto is on the list.
          Akumal is on the list. Probably somewhere we haven't been yet is also on the list.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">The bigger picture</h2>
        <p>
          Building toward a life that works from a café in Porto as easily as it does from Missouri.
          The work is interesting. The goal is flexibility. Those two things are, it turns out,
          not in conflict.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
